# Glowtone
Not the block! A utility mod providing easy resource-pack block and item emissives without bloat. Check the [Gallery](https://modrinth.com/project/glowtone/gallery) for beatuiful examples from our built-in resource-pack!

## How it works
Glowtone is simple. Textures with a suffix of `_glowtone_emissive` are used on performant, auto-generated model overlays. Light level can be set on a per-texture basis via `.mcmeta` like the following example:
```json
{
  "glowtone_emissive": {
    "light_emission": 15
  }
}
```
And last of all, render layers for block can be overrode on a per-block basis via `glowtone_block_render_type_overwrites/<block>.json`, like so:
```json
{
  "render_type": "cutout"
}
```


Use the built-in resource-pack for Vanilla emissives, or bring your own! Take a look at [our pack](https://github.com/FrozenBlock/Glowtone/tree/main/src/main/resources/resourcepacks/glowtone_emissives) for example useage if you want to set up compatability for your own mods or want to make resource-packs.

Does not mess with shaders. Should work out-of-the-box with Iris and Core Shaders!
